CheckedListBox.CheckedIndexCollection Class

Definition

Encapsulates the collection of indexes of checked items (including items in an indeterminate state) in a CheckedListBox.

In this Article

public class CheckedListBox.CheckedIndexCollection : System.Collections.IList
Inheritance
System.Object
CheckedListBox.CheckedIndexCollection

Inherited Members

Equals(Object)
Equals(Object,Object)
GetHashCode()
GetType()
MemberwiseClone()
ReferenceEquals(Object,Object)
ToString()

Remarks

The checked indexes collection is a subset of the indexes into the collection of all items in the CheckedListBox control. These indexes specify items in a checked or indeterminate state.

The following table is an example of the indexed collection of items in the control (all items contained in the control).

Index Item Check State
0 object 1 CheckState
1 object 2 CheckState
2 object 3 CheckState
3 object 4 CheckState
4 object 5 CheckState

Based on the previous example, the following table shows the indexed collection of indexes of checked items.

Index Index of Item
0 1
1 3
2 4

The CheckedListBox class has two members that allow you to access the stored indexes, the Item property and the IndexOf method.

Based on the previous example, a call to the Item property with a parameter value of 1 returns a value of 3. A call to IndexOf with a parameter of 3 returns a value of 1.

Properties

Count

Gets the number of checked items.

public int Count { get; }
Value
Int32

The number of indexes in the collection.

IsReadOnly

Gets a value indicating whether the collection is read-only.

public bool IsReadOnly { get; }
Value
Boolean

true in all cases.

Item(Int32)

Gets the index of a checked item in the CheckedListBox control.

public int this[int index] { get; }
index
Int32

An index into the checked indexes collection. This index specifies the index of the checked item you want to retrieve.

Value
Int32

The index of the checked item. For more information, see the examples in the CheckedListBox.CheckedIndexCollection class overview.

Exceptions
ArgumentException

The index is less than zero.

-or-

The index is not in the collection.

Remarks

The index parameter is an index into the checked indexes collection. The return value is the corresponding indexed value, which is the index of the checked item in the items collection.

Methods

Contains(Int32)

Determines whether the specified index is located in the collection.

public bool Contains (int index);
index
Int32

The index to locate in the collection.

Returns
Boolean

true if the specified index from the CheckedListBox.ObjectCollection is an item in this collection; otherwise, false.

Remarks

You can use this method to determine whether an index from the Items collection is in the CheckedIndices collection.

CopyTo(Array,Int32)

Copies the entire collection into an existing array at a specified location within the array.

public void CopyTo (Array dest, int index);
dest
Array

The destination array.

index
Int32

The zero-based relative index in dest at which copying begins.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

array is null.

RankException

array is multidimensional.

ArgumentOutOfRangeException

index is less than zero.

ArgumentException

The number of elements in the source Array is greater than the available space from index to the end of the destination Array.

ArrayTypeMismatchException

The type of the source Array cannot be cast automatically to the type of the destination Array.

Remarks

You can use this method to combine the selected indexes from multiple collections into a single array.

GetEnumerator()

Returns an enumerator that can be used to iterate through the stem.Windows.Forms.CheckedListBox.CheckedIndices* collection.

public System.Collections.IEnumerator GetEnumerator ();
Returns
IEnumerator

An IEnumerator for navigating through the list.

IndexOf(Int32)

Returns an index into the collection of checked indexes.

public int IndexOf (int index);
index
Int32

The index of the checked item.

Returns
Int32

The index that specifies the index of the checked item or -1 if the index parameter is not in the checked indexes collection. For more information, see the examples in the CheckedListBox.CheckedIndexCollection class overview.

Remarks

The index parameter is the index of a checked item in the items collection. The return value is the corresponding index into the checked indexes collection.
